A Netcare 911 helicopter has crashed at Bergville in western KwaZulu-Natal.  Netcare says in a statement that everyone on board died in the crash. The helicopter was carrying a pilot and four health care workers when it crashed on Thursday. Netcare 911 spokesperson Martina Nicholson says they are saddened by the crash and has expressed Netcare’s sympathy with the families of the victims. She adds that the details surrounding the crash are not clear. 